==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Music drama
<hw>Mu"sic dra`ma</hw>. <def>An opera in which the text and action are
not interrupted by set arias, duets, etc., the music being determined
throughout by dramatic appropriateness; musical drama of this character,
in general. It involves the use of a kind of melodious declamation, the
development of leitmotif, great orchestral elaboration, and a fusion of
poetry, music, action, and scene into an organic whole. The term is
applied esp. to the later works of Wagner: ⟦ldquo⟧Tristan und
Isolde,⟦rdquo⟧ ⟦ldquo⟧Die Meistersinger,⟦rdquo⟧ ⟦ldquo⟧Rheingold,⟦rdquo⟧
⟦ldquo⟧Walk⟦uum⟧re,⟦rdquo⟧ ⟦ldquo⟧Siegfried,⟦rdquo⟧
⟦ldquo⟧G⟦oum⟧tterd⟦aum⟧mmerung,⟦rdquo⟧ and
⟦ldquo⟧Parsifal.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Music hall</ent>⟦br⟧
